{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Do not introduce the Plan 5 student loan repayment plan from August 2023",
        "additional_details": "I believe this new repayment plan greatly jeopardises the future of students who choose to attend university, and could put many off from going to university. I strongly recommend the Government abandon this reform, and keeps the current repayment system, which I believe is fairer.",
        "background": "I believe that the new Plan 5 repayment system is greatly unfair and off-putting for new university students. Students should not have to repay the loan at a lower threshold. Maintaining the Plan 2 repayment threshold would allow graduates to more financially secure.",
